reac-tools is a pure-Python toolkit for analysing captured Roland REAC
(audio-over-Ethernet, EtherType 0x8819) traffic: parsing tcpdump text /
classic pcap captures and reporting datagram loss, reorder, duplication,
A/B cross-mixing and inter-arrival jitter.

## Third-party code and references

All source files in this repository are original works. No third-party
code is copied or otherwise included; this repository therefore carries
no third-party copyright. The references below document where the REAC
wire-protocol *facts* re-implemented here came from.

### Protocol facts referenced (no code reused, no upstream copyright)

The following projects reverse-engineered and documented the REAC wire
framing. reac-tools re-implements those documented facts in original
Python -- locating the 0x8819 EtherType, stripping any 802.1Q tag, and
reading the 16-bit little-endian sequence counter from the first two
payload bytes -- without copying any code or structure from them:

- per-gron/reacdriver -- GPL-3.0. The original REAC reverse-engineering
  (macOS driver). Documents the wire framing: EtherType 0x8819, the 16-bit
  little-endian sequence counter at payload bytes 0-1, the 0xC2 0xEA end
  marker, and the 1492-byte frame. Used as the primary framing reference.
- norihiro/obs-h8819-source -- GPL-3.0-or-later -- Copyright (C) 2022
  Norihiro Kamae <norihiro@nagater.net>. OBS REAC source plugin, framing
  taken from reacdriver. Confirms the same 16-bit little-endian
  `l2_counter` and per-frame +1 sequencing used here.

These facts inform the original implementations in `reac/model.py`,
`reac/parser.py`, `reac/pcap.py`, `tools/make_fixture.py`, and the
fixtures embedded in `tests/test_parser.py`. None of these files derive
from upstream code; they re-express publicly documented protocol facts.

### Standards and specifications (facts, not copyrightable, no claim)

- libpcap classic savefile format -- file magic 0xA1B2C3D4, global and
  per-packet headers (referenced by `reac/pcap.py`, an original
  struct-based reader/writer; no libpcap code is used).
- IEEE 802.1Q -- VLAN tag layout, for stripping the phantom tag seen on
  bridge egress (`reac/parser.py`, `reac/pcap.py`).

The interface facts of the Roland REAC protocol (EtherType, framing,
sequence counter) are stated as facts and carry no copyright claim by this
project.
